-- @expect-error: escape the handler
-- The handler instantiates parameter $p and handles get : Unit ~> $p, so the
-- row-level check is satisfied. But the body leaks the $p-typed result through
-- the outer variable f (forcing f : $p -> _), so $p escapes the handler into
-- the context. The no-escape side condition dom(s) cap fpv(D, G) = {} must
-- reject this; without the check the program wrongly infers a type mentioning $p.
return (fun f ->
  with handler {
    $p -> Int,
    return x -> return x,
    get a k -> k 5
  } handle (
    effect !get : Unit ~> $p.
    do x <- !get () in
    f x
  ))
